==English==

===Noun===
'''[[abiding]]-[[place]]'''
# The place where one [[abide]]s; a permanent dwelling-place; hence, a place of rest; a resting-place.

====Quotations====
* {{RQ:Hardy Laodicean}}, Book III, Chapter 7
*: ...for having no other commission he determined (...) to make, as before, the castle itself his office, studio, and chief '''abiding-place''' till the works were fairly in progress.

